item.title: [HIVE-18920] CBO: Initialize the Janino providers ahead of 1st query
item.description:
Hive Calcite metadata providers are compiled when the 1st query comes in.

If a second query arrives before the 1st one has built a metadata provider, it will also try to do the same thing, because the cache is not populated yet.

With 1024 concurrent users, it takes 6 minutes for the 1st query to finish fighting all the other queries which are trying to load that cache.
item.summary: CBO: Initialize the Janino providers ahead of 1st query

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Can this be done at HS2 process startup time?
Last I checked, this accidentally happens when MV registry starts up.
then it is no longer an issue? jcamachorodriguez can you please confirm and resolve.
ashutoshc, gopalv, I believe that would happen if we have at least one materialized view in the system. However, that may not always be the case. I am working on it right now.

-1 overall
